#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.32"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.32:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.32:0.2"
msgid "3. Sabbavagga "
msgstr "3. All "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 32. Dutiyasamugghātasappāyasutta → dutiyasappāyapaṭipadāsuttaṃ (bj) | sappāya 2 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.32:0.3"
msgid "32. Dutiyasamugghātasappāyasutta "
msgstr "32. The Practice Conducive to Uprooting (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.32:1.1"
msgid "“Sabbamaññitasamugghātasappāyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, paṭipadaṃ desessāmi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you the practice that’s conducive to uprooting all identifying. "

msgctxt "sn35.32:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha. "
msgstr "Listen … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.32:1.3"
msgid "Katamā ca sā, bhikkhave, sabbamaññitasamugghātasappāyā paṭipadā? "
msgstr "And what is the practice that’s conducive to uprooting all identifying? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.32:2.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn35.32:2.2"
msgid "cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.32:3.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.32:4.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.25, sc5
msgctxt "sn35.32:5.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn35.32:6.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn35.32:6.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn35.32:7.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn35.32:8.1"
msgid "“Rūpā … pe … "
msgstr "“Are sights … "

msgctxt "sn35.32:8.2"
msgid "cakkhuviññāṇaṃ … "
msgstr "eye consciousness … "

#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn35.32:9.1"
msgid "cakkhusamphasso nicco vā anicco vā”ti? "
msgstr "eye contact … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.32:9.2"
msgid "“Anicco, bhante” … pe …. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn35.32:10.1"
msgid "“Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "The pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact: is that permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn35.32:11.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn35.32:12.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn35.32:13.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn35.32:14.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn35.32:14.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "sn35.32:15.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante” … pe …. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "sn35.32:16.1"
msgid "“Jivhā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti? "
msgstr "“Is the ear … nose … tongue … "

msgctxt "sn35.32:16.2"
msgid "“Aniccā, bhante” … pe …. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "sn35.32:18.1"
msgid "“Rasā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.32:18.2"
msgid "jivhāviññāṇaṃ … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.32:18.3"
msgid "jivhāsamphasso … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.32:18.4"
msgid "yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "sn35.32:19.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.32:19.2"
msgid "dhammā … "
msgstr "body … mind … "

msgctxt "sn35.32:19.3"
msgid "manoviññāṇaṃ … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.32:19.4"
msgid "manosamphasso nicco vā anicco vā”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "sn35.32:20.1"
msgid "“Anicco, bhante”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "sn35.32:21.1"
msgid "“Yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "The pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact: is that permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "sn35.32:22.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "sn35.32:23.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "sn35.32:24.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "sn35.32:25.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn35.32:25.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc26
msgctxt "sn35.32:26.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.26, sc27
msgctxt "sn35.32:27.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati. "
msgstr "“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.32:27.2"
msgid "Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati … pe … "
msgstr "And they grow disillusioned with the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.32:27.3"
msgid "jivhāyapi nibbindati, rasesupi … pe … yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati … pe …. "
msgstr "They grow disillusioned with the ear … nose … tongue … body … "

msgctxt "sn35.32:27.4"
msgid "Manasmimpi nibbindati, dhammesupi nibbindati, manoviññāṇepi nibbindati, manosamphassepi nibbindati. "
msgstr "They grow disillusioned with the mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, and mind contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.32:27.5"
msgid "Yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati. "
msgstr "And they grow disillusioned with the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.32:27.6"
msgid "Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.32:27.7"
msgid "‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’ "

msgctxt "sn35.32:27.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho sā, bhikkhave, sabbamaññitasamugghātasappāyā paṭipadā”ti. "
msgstr "This is the practice that’s conducive to uprooting all identifying.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.32:27.9"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.32:27.10"
msgid "Sabbavaggo tatiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc28
msgctxt "sn35.32:28.1"
msgid "Sabbañca dvepi pahānā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.32:28.2"
msgid "parijānāpare duve; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.32:28.3"
msgid "Ādittaṃ addhabhūtañca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.32:28.4"
msgid "sāruppā dve ca sappāyā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.32:28.5"
msgid "Vaggo tena pavuccatīti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
